   > [...] still don't know precisely what
   > randomness *is*, or how one tests a bit stream for it.

I recommend purchasing the book which contains the proceedings
of CRYPTO-90; it has a lot of applicable material:

    A. J. Menzes and S. A. Vanstone, editors, "Advances in
    Cryptology - CRYPTO 90", Springer-Verlag, Berlin, 1991,
    ISBN 0-387-54508-5 (NY), ISBN 3-540-54508-5 (Germany).
    Approx $50.00 at Computer Literacy Bookshop.


Especially noteworthy is Chapter 9, which includes:

    Ueli M. Maurer, "A Universal Statistical Test for Random
    Bit Generators", proceedings of CRYPPTO-90, pp. 409-420.

-- M. Johnson
